{
  "texts": [
    "The scenario of imbalanced semisupervised learning is commonly observed in real-world settings [48] [49] [50] [51].",
    "To verify the generalizability of our model, we further evaluated our model on four benchmark datasets.",
    "To simulate an imbalanced setting, we set the imbalance ratio γ of 5 for labeled data and 150 for unlabeled data, a common setting in image classification 37.",
    "For example, for AG News dataset in setting 1, the case numbers across four categories are [40, 23, 13, 8].",
    "In setting 2, the number distribution is [200, 116, 68, 40]."
  ]
}